meta {
  name: IntegratorStart
  type: http
  seq: 1
}

post {
  url: https://lynx.nayax.com/payment/v2/transactions/Cortina/{{integrator_name}}/start
  body: json
  auth: none
}

body:json {
  {
    "AppUserId": "USER_ID_FROM_APP",
    "SecretToken": "{{secret_token}}",
    "TerminalId": "TERMINAL_HW_SERIAL",
    "TransactionId": "UNIQUE_TXN_ID_MIN_8_CHARS",
    "Balance": 0
  }
}

docs {
  Direction: Integrator → Nayax (EXCEPTION — this is the only Cortina endpoint on Nayax's server).
  Server: https://lynx.nayax.com/payment/v2/transactions (override from spec)
  Sandbox: https://qa-lynx.nayax.com/payment/v2/transactions/Cortina/{integratorName}/start

  Called by the integrator when a user scans a Static QR code. Notifies Nayax that
  a user is at the machine and ready to pay.

  SecretToken: 64-char key provided by Nayax — registered per integrator name.
  TerminalId: HW serial of the vending machine (printed on sticker / encoded in QR).
  TransactionId: Unique per transaction, minimum 8 chars.
  AppUserId: Unique consumer ID in the Mobile App provider's system.

  Live test 2026-05-15:
  - Both lynx.nayax.com and qa-lynx.nayax.com are reachable
  - All requests with unregistered SecretToken return: {"Status":{"Verdict":"Declined","Code":13}}
  - Code 13 = NOT listed in StaticQR decline reasons table (doc gap — likely Invalid SecretToken)
  - Field validation does not fire before SecretToken check
}

